Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high
heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Thai Green Style Paste{45%g} and @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}
(less if you'd prefer things milder), ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Coconut Milk{180%ml} and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}.

Add the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{240%g}. Bring to the boil, then lower the
heat. Simmer, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no
> pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @Lime{1}.

Once thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} in handfuls, making sure it's piping
hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Squeeze in some lime juice. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lime juice if needed.

Fluff up the rice and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the curry.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!